text:
{
  "prompt": "A delivery box designed for an electric bicycle, large enough to hold a 60-liter Papa John's family-size pizza. The box includes a built-in secondary battery system underneath or on one side. It is mounted on a rear rack of an e-bike. The box is rectangular, sturdy, and insulated, with secure latches. The battery compartment is water-resistant, with a visible connector cable to the main bike frame. Show the pizza box partially inside the compartment to indicate size compatibility. Urban background with a bike parked for delivery.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A concept design of a low-center-of-gravity electric motorcycle with a skateboard-style base. The frame is minimalist and streamlined, with a wide foot platform resembling a skateboard deck. The wheels are mismatched for comfort and traction: a 20-inch slim front wheel and an 18-inch wide rear tire. The seat is plush and wide with lumbar support, optimized for all-day urban delivery use. The battery is integrated under the deck for low center of mass. The front features a clean LED headlight, and the rear has a large 60L cargo box that can fit a Papa John's family-sized pizza and an auxiliary battery. The design blends classic scooter curves with modern electric components, shown in a side view with no rider, parked against a neutral background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution digital photograph of a sleek, low-riding electric scooter with a matte black finish and front fairing (front cowl) installed. The scooter features a retro-modern design, low step-through deck like a skateboard, comfortable cushioned seat, chrome handlebars with mirrors, and a compact rear cargo box. The front cowl is aerodynamic and smoothly integrated around the headlamp and handlebar area. The vehicle is parked on clean asphalt in daylight, casting soft shadows. The overall appearance is refined and urban, emphasizing comfort and stability.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution daytime photograph of a stylish electric scooter on an asphalt surface. The scooter features a modern, aerodynamic white body with bold red accents on the front cowl, rims, and seat stitching. The design is sleek and minimalist with a low, skateboard-style frame for a low center of gravity. It has a comfortable ergonomic seat, chrome mirrors, and a matching red-accented rear cargo box. The lighting highlights the clean lines and stylish contrast of the red and white color scheme.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic, stylish white electric scooter with aerodynamic red accents, featuring a tinted windshield and a sporty, aggressive design. The scooter is parked on smooth gray asphalt and viewed from a three-quarter angle. It has a sleek, streamlined front fairing with integrated turn signals, low-profile red alloy wheels, a sculpted red seat, and an aerodynamic rear cargo box. The overall design emphasizes aerodynamic performance, with smooth curves, minimal drag surfaces, and a performance-oriented riding position.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed technical line drawing of an electric motorcycle frame designed with a skateboard-style base for housing a large battery pack. The frame includes mounting points for a 4000W hub motor, double front suspension, dual rear gas shock absorbers, ABS and TCS systems. The frame should have a low and long profile, allowing for a 72V 200Ah battery installed flat in the lower section. The drawing should show the side view (profile), highlighting key elements like battery compartment, motor mount, swingarm pivots, seat post area, and possible windshield/cowl mounts. Industrial, clean, minimal blueprint aesthetic, white background with dark lines.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A schematic diagram of a dual-path power transmission system for an electric motorcycle. The diagram should include the following components: Motor at the top center, with two arrows splitting downward. The left arrow leads to a 2-speed gearbox labeled 'Low/Medium Speed Gearbox', then to a chainring, chain, rear cog, hub, and rear tire. The right arrow leads directly to another chainring labeled 'Direct Drive for High Speed', which also connects to the rear cog, hub, and rear tire. Use clear labels for each component. The layout should be clean, technical, and symmetrical.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
